nburgh]]\n| National leaders\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| {{Yes|'''P'''}}<br /><small>[[Nicola Sturgeon|Sturgeon]]</small>\n| {{Yes|'''P'''}}<br /><small>[[Tim Farron|Farron]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | 5 June<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2017/utv-election-debate-nigel-dodds-to-deputise-for-arlene-foster-35787569.html |title=UTV election debate: Nigel Dodds to deputise for Arlene Foster|newspaper=Belfasttelegraph.co.uk}}</ref>\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[UTV (TV channel)|UTV]]\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[Belfast]]\n| Northern Ireland\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <small>[[Nigel Dodds]] ([[Democratic Unionist Party|DUP]]), [[Michelle O'Neill]] ([[Sinn F\u00e9in|SF]]), [[Robin Swann]] ([[Ulster Unionist Party|UUP]]), [[Colum Eastwood]] ([[Social Democratic and Labour Party|SDLP]]) and [[Naomi Long]] ([[Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|APNI]])</small>\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | 6 June<ref name=\":STV:\" />\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[STV (TV channel)|STV]]\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[Glasgow]]\n| Scottish leaders\n| {{Yes|'''P'''<br /><small>[[Ruth Davidson|Davidson]]</small>}}\n| {{Yes|'''P'''<br /><small>[[Kezia Dugdale|Dugdale]]</small>}}\n| {{Yes|'''P'''<br /><small>[[Nicola Sturgeon|Sturgeon]]</small>}}\n| {{Yes|'''P'''<br /><small>[[Willie Rennie|Rennie]]</small>}}\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n| style=\"background:#A2B2C2; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''NI'''\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | 6 June\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[BBC]] Newsbeat <ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/40182474/election-2017-what-you-said-in-the-final-debate |title = Election 2017: What you said in the Final Debate|date = 6 June 2017}}</ref>\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[Manchester]]\n| National leaders\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>[[Nadhim Zahawi|Zahawi]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>[[Sarah Champion (politician)|Champion]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>[[Kate Forbes|Forbes]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>[[Brian Paddick, Baron Paddick|Paddick]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>Fflur Elin</small>\n| {{Yes|'''P'''}}<br /><small>[[Jonathan Bartley|Bartley]]</small>\n| style=\"background:#D0F0C0; color:black; text-align:center;\" | '''S'''<br /><small>[[David Kurten|Kurten]]</small>\n|-\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | 6 June\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[BBC]]\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | [[Belfast]]\n| Northern Ireland leaders\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | <small>[[Jeffrey Donaldson]] ([[Democratic Unionist Party|DUP]]), [[John O'Dowd]] ([[Sinn F\u00e9in|SF]]), [[Robin Swann]] ([[Ulster Unionist Party|UUP]]), [[Colum Eastwood]] ([[Social Democratic and Labour Party|SDLP]]) and [[Naomi Long]] ([[Alliance Party of Northern Ireland|APNI]])</small>\n|}\n\n===Campaign costs===\nIn the 12 months leading up to the election, the Conservatives spent \u00a318.5m, Labour spent \u00a311m and the Liberal Democrats spent \u00a36.8m.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/19/electoral-commission-conservatives-spent-lost-majority-2017-election|title=Tories spent \u00a318.5m on election that cost them majority|first=Peter Walker Political|last=correspondent|date=19 March 2018|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Endorsements==\n{{Main|Endorsements in the 2017 United Kingdom general election}}\nNewspapers, organisations and individuals endorsed parties or individual candidates for the election. For example, the main national newspapers gave the following endorsements:\n\n===National daily newspapers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Newspapers\n! colspan=2| Endorsement\n! Notes\n! 2017 circulation (June)<ref name=\"DP\">{{cite news |url=https://www.pressgazette.co.uk/daily-mail-and-sun-launch-front-page-attacks-on-corbyn-as-fleet-street-lines-up-behind-theresa-may/ |title=Daily Mail and Sun launch front-page attacks on Corbyn as Fleet Street lines up behind Theresa May |last=Ponsford |first=Dominic |date=7 June 2017 |work=[[Press Gazette]]}}</ref>\n! Link\n|-\n| ''[[Daily Express]]''\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]\n|\n| 386,297\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=VOTE MAY OR WE FACE DISASTER: It's time for patriotic realism NOT socialist indulgence |url=http://www.express.co.uk/comment/expresscomment/813903/general-election-2017-Conservatives-Theresa-May-UK-campaign-Daily-Express |website=Daily Express |date=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Daily Mail]]''\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]\n|\n| 1,454,073\n|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/03/which-parties-are-the-uk-press-backing-in-the-general-election |title=Which parties are the UK press backing in the general election? |last=McKee |first=Ruth |work=The Guardian |date=3 June 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Daily Mirror]]''\n| style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]]\n| On electio