 politics after almost 30 years |last=Oliver |first=Matt |work=Oxford Mail |date=19 April 2017 |access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Gisela|Stuart}}\n| [[Birmingham Edgbaston (UK Parliament constituency)|Birmingham Edgbaston]]\n| [[1997 United Kingdom general election|1997]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| {{dts|19 April 2017}}<ref>{{cite news |url=http://labour-uncut.co.uk/2017/04/19/gisela-stuart-quits/ |title=Gisela Stuart quits |work=Labour Uncut |date=19 April 2017 |accessdate=19 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Michelle|Thomson}}\n| [[Edinburgh West (UK Parliament constituency)|Edinburgh West]]\n| [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Independent politician|Independent]] {{small|([[Scottish National Party|SNP]] in 2015)}}\n| {{dts|22 April 2017}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/jamieross/michelle-thomson-will-step-down-as-an-mp-after-the-snp |title=Michelle Thomson Will Step Down As An MP After The SNP Ruled She Can't Stand For Them |work=Buzzfeed News |date=22 April 2017 |accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Andrew|Turner|Andrew Turner (politician)}}\n| [[Isle of Wight (UK Parliament constituency)|Isle of Wight]]\n| [[2001 United Kingdom general election|2001]]\n| width=\"1\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n| {{dts|28 April 2017}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-39749203 |title=Isle of Wight MP steps down after 'gay danger remark' |date=28 April 2017 |work=BBC News|access-date=29 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Andrew|Tyrie|Andrew Tyrie}}\n| [[Chichester (UK Parliament constituency)|Chichester]]\n| [[1997 United Kingdom general election|1997]]\n| width=\"1\" bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n| {{dts|25 April 2017}}<ref>{{ci