arked in bold. The age listed is the age at the end of that last tournament, i.e., the age at which the player completed his Career Grand Slam.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!width=150| Player\n!style=\"background:#ffc; width=130; font-weight:bold;\"|[[Australian Open]]\n!style=\"background:#ebc2af; width=130; font-weight:bold;\"|[[French Open]]\n!style=\"background:#cfc; width=130; font-weight:bold;\"|[[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]]\n!style=\"background:#ccf; width=130; font-weight:bold;\"|[[US Open (tennis)|US Open]]\n!width=150| Age\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|GBR}} [[Fred Perry]] || [[1934 Australian Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1934]] || '''[[1935 French Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1935]]''' || [[1934 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1934]] || [[1933 U.S. National Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1933]] || align=\"left\"|26 years, 15 days\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|USA|1912}} [[Don Budge]] || [[1938 Australian Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1938]] || '''[[1938 French Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1938]]''' || [[1937 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1937]] || [[1937 U.S. National Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1937]] || align=\"left\"|22 years, 357 days\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Rod Laver]] || [[1960 Australian Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1960]] || [[1962 French Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1962]] || [[1961 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1961]] || '''[[1962 U.S. National Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1962]]''' || align=\"left\"|24 years, 32 days\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Roy Emerson]] || [[1961 Australian Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1961]] || [[1963 French Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1963]] || '''[[1964 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1964]]''' || [[1961 U.S. National Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1961]] || align=\"left\"|27 years, 244 days\n|-\n| align=\"left\"|{{